Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Euler's Number
Formula: e ≈ 2.71828182845...
Note:    Base of natural logarithm; fundamental to calculus

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Euler's Identity
Formula: e^(iπ) + 1 = 0
Note:    Relates five fundamental constants; called most beautiful equation

Domain:  Chemistry
Topic:   pH Definition
Formula: pH = -log[H+]
Note:    Measure of hydrogen ion concentration; 7 is neutral

Domain:  Physics
Topic:   2nd Law of Thermodynamics
Formula: ΔS ≥ 0
Note:    Entropy always increases in isolated systems

Domain:  Mathematics
Topic:   Bayes Theorem
Formula: P(A|B) = P(B|A)P(A)/P(B)
Note:    Updating probability based on new evidence

